	(1146,146,'main_modules_1_person_2_bio','Philip is a Portfolio Manager at Tatton. Prior to this, he worked in various fields of the financial services industry. He began his career as an equities broker and contributed to the company’s daily market and economic briefing. He then became a proprietary futures trader where he gained experience in commodity, fixed income and equity markets, along with implementing systematic strategies. He then joined a global macro hedge fund as an investment analyst. He holds a BSc in Software Engineering and an MBA in Technology Management from Queen Mary University of London. He also holds the CISI regulations and securities certificates and is a Chartered Financial Analyst (CFA) Level III candidate.'),
