	(1156,146,'main_modules_1_person_3_bio','Alex is the Chief Investment Consultant leading the imparting of the Tatton investment philosophy to the financial adviser community and their clients. He has been in the financial services industry since 1986 and has held senior positions at Friends Provident, Foreign &amp; Colonial Asset Management, Octopus Investments and Nationwide Financial Services. Alex was educated in Holland, Germany and England. He holds an LLB (Hons) in Law, a BSc (Hons) in mathematics, a BA (Hons) in German and the Diploma in Financial Planning (DipPFS). As a renowned expert for the cross-section between investments and product, Alex will be invaluable in advising firms on the most suitable application of Tatton’s platform focused investment strategies.'),
