	(264,1,'2015-11-10 20:40:37','2015-11-10 20:40:37','Lothar Mentel is Chief Executive Officer for Tatton Investment Management. Prior to setting up Tatton IM in 2012, Lothar was the CIO for Octopus Investments since 2008, where he built a multi manager fund business that he grew to £1.6bn. Before that, he held senior positions with NM Rothschild, Threadneedle, Barclays Wealth and Commerzbank Asset Management. He began his career in Germany as a performance and risk analyst and later designed and launched the Barclays Multi Manager funds. Lothar is a regular contributor to industry conferences, publications and industry body work-groups. He has over 20 years’ investment management experience. Lothar was educated in Germany and holds a postgraduate degree in Business and Economics (Diplom Oekonom) from Rhur-Universitaet Bochum.','Lothar Mentel','','publish','closed','closed','','lothar-mentel','','','2015-11-13 16:10:26','2015-11-13 16:10:26','',0,'http://tatton.dev/?post_type=people&#038;p=264',0,'people','',0),
	(265,1,'2015-11-10 20:45:12','2015-11-10 20:45:12','Steven is Head of Investment Management at Tatton. He has over 10 years of investment industry experience. Prior to joining Tatton he was a member of the investment strategy team responsible for running the £18bn UK Railways Pension Scheme, an economist for the British Government planning future pension provision (NEST) and an investment consultant for a boutique private wealth management firm. He holds a First Class BSc in Economics, an MSc in Economics from The London School of Economics and an MSc in International Securities, Investment &amp; Banking from the ICMA Centre Business School. He is a Chartered Financial Analyst (CFA).','Steven Keshishoghli, CFA','','publish','closed','closed','','steven-keshishoghli-cfa','','','2015-11-13 16:12:04','2015-11-13 16:12:04','',0,'http://tatton.dev/?post_type=people&#038;p=265',0,'people','',0),
	(266,1,'2015-11-10 20:46:09','2015-11-10 20:46:09','<p class=\"p1\">Philip is a Portfolio Manager at Tatton. Prior to this, he worked in various fields of the financial services industry. He began his career as an equities broker and contributed to the company’s daily market and economic briefing. He then became a proprietary futures trader where he gained experience in commodity, fixed income and equity markets, along with implementing systematic strategies. He then joined a global macro hedge fund as an investment analyst. He holds a BSc in Software Engineering and an MBA in Technology Management from Queen Mary University of London. He also holds the CISI regulations and securities certificates and is a Chartered Financial Analyst (CFA) Level III candidate.</p>','Philip Riris','','publish','closed','closed','','philip-riris','','','2015-11-10 21:35:52','2015-11-10 21:35:52','',0,'http://tatton.dev/?post_type=people&#038;p=266',0,'people','',0),
	(267,1,'2015-11-10 20:46:31','2015-11-10 20:46:31','<p class=\"p1\">Alex is the Chief Investment Consultant leading the imparting of the Tatton investment philosophy to the financial adviser community and their clients. He has been in the financial services industry since 1986 and has held senior positions at Friends Provident, Foreign &amp; Colonial Asset Management, Octopus Investments and Nationwide Financial Services. Alex was educated in Holland, Germany and England. He holds an LLB (Hons) in Law, a BSc (Hons) in mathematics, a BA (Hons) in German and the Diploma in Financial Planning (DipPFS). As a renowned expert for the cross-section between investments and product, Alex will be invaluable in advising firms on the most suitable application of Tatton’s platform focused investment strategies.</p>','Alex Antonius','','publish','closed','closed','','alex-antonius','','','2015-11-10 21:36:11','2015-11-10 21:36:11','',0,'http://tatton.dev/?post_type=people&#038;p=267',0,'people','',0),
